cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper investigates strategies to reduce communication delay in wireless networks.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses probabilistic delay and effective capacity to evaluate performance, which are concepts from information theory.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper focuses on millimeter wave communications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible as the paper considers a hybrid scheme that combines traffic dispersion and network densification.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security issues related to low latency communications.
